    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith clangd LSP server (also tried others), when the auto-trigger keyword is triggered (`.` or `->` for a structure), it always pre-select the first item, not allowing me to continue typing. But have to `C-e` to cancel the completion then type, then manually trigger completion manually.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nMinimal config:\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config['clangd'] = {\n  cmd = { 'clangd' },\n  filetypes = { 'c' },\n  root_markers = { 'compile_commands.json' },\n}\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n  callback = function(ev)\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(ev.data.client_id)\n\n    if client:supports_method('textDocument/completion') then\n      vim.lsp.completion.enable(true, client.id, ev.buf, { autotrigger = true })\n    end\n  end\n})\n```\n\nEnter the project (in my case it's the linux kernel), and edit the file `fs/btrfs/disk-io.c`.\nInside a context where there is an extent buffer structure, trigger the auto-completion will result\nthe following pre-selection of the first item:\n\n<img width=\"880\" height=\"576\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f1ee3970-64c4-4118-b847-70e3c79039b2\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAt least some way to configure if auto-completion should pre-select the first item.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.5\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nclangd 21.1.6\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
